cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image-to-image translation using deep convolutional and conditional generative adversarial networks (GANs), which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses unsupervised learning, which is a subfield of ML, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of GANs also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. The paper also mentions applications such as bidirectional translation, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
